Follow `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and the docs in `docs/` as the source of truth.

Lumen standards:
- privacy-first, local-first, Apple-native
- App Store-quality and portfolio-quality
- one concern per PR
- one logical change per commit
- prefer native SwiftUI/iOS APIs over layout hacks
- avoid over-engineering and unrelated cleanup
- do not port Enchanted complexity wholesale
- preserve clean diffs and reviewer-friendly structure

Priority order:
1. architecture and core abstractions
2. integration points
3. risky unknowns / spike work
4. implementation
5. polish later

Parallel work rules:
- branch per task
- micro-PRD driven
- do not run multiple agents on shared shell/settings/provider files without coordination

Before calling work done:
- run relevant validation
- be honest about anything not validated
- keep the PR clean and tightly scoped
